Why is Northern Dynasty Minerals (NYSE MKT: NAK) recommended on your site?
The NAK Stock was added in early 2017 because it has been identified as a stock with a serious upside potential.
Below are several reasons to consider Northern Dynasty Minerals (NAK):
						   
They have the world's largest undeveloped copper & gold resource.
They have massive known resources - 6.44 Billion tonnes of Measured/Indicated and 4.46 Billion tonnes of Inferred.
They not only have Gold & Copper, but they also have massive reserves of Silver & Molybdenum.
The current value of one of their resources alone (eg. Silver) is worth many times their current market cap (as of July 2017).
They reached a settlement with the EPA and are their way to permitting, which ends the unfair treatment against them from the Obama era.
We now have an administration who understands and wants a fair, normal, and predictable permitting process for companies.
The state of Alaska, and the USA as a whole, needs the jobs and extra revenue that will be generated from their Pebble mine.
They are led by a professional and proven management team.
There is large institutional ownership (around 30% as of June 2017). When institutions invest, it is a good sign of things to come.
They have large insider ownership. When management invests in their own company, it is in their best interest to make the company succeed.
They will be finding partner(s) anytime now. It is planned to happen by end of Q3 2017. This will be a major catalyst for bullish stock movement.











